<item>
            <title>[HIVE-12603] Add config to block queries that scan &gt; N number of partitions </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-12603</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Strict mode is useful for blocking queries that load all partitions, but it&apos;s still possible to put significant load on the HMS for queries that scan a large number of partitions. It would be useful to add a config provide a hard limit to the number of partitions scanned by a query.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
